DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros('PGstandard.pl', 'PGML.pl', 'parserPopUp.pl', 'PGcourse.pl');

$r = random(-.975,-.75,.025);

$dd = DropDown([['positive', 'negative', 'zero', 'it cannot be determined']],1);

$rsq = $r**2;

BEGIN_PGML

The linear correlation coefficient of a set of data points is [`[$r]`]. 

a) What is the sign of the slope of the regression line? [_]{$dd}

b) Determine the coefficient of determination. [_]{Real($rsq)}

END_PGML

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
a) If the correlation coefficient is negative, then the slope is also *negative*. 

b) The coefficient of determination is [`r^2= ([$r])^2 = [$rsq] `].
END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.